text.text:
Cafe in the day, and Bistro at night, we were there for a buffet lunch. The highlight was the lobster porridge (paofan). Apart from that,  they served the usual finger food, so nothing much to brag about.

If you want desserts, then go for their waffles with the mango passion fruit flavour.

text.text: Good meal before catching a football match at Jalan Besar Stadium. Value for money using Burpple. Fish and chips is nice. Very nice head chef and staff. Will come back to try the waffles.

text.text: The staff are friendly and patient. Service was pretty good too. Spacious and clean with a simple design. Ai Cafe is great for a relaxed dining experience with friends and family. Most importantly, the food is nice and price is reasonable too!

text.text: This cafe by day and bar at night is located in a comfy shophouse along Horne. Lunch set meal was priced at 19 sgd ++ to include one of 3 main courses, a soda drink, mushroom soup and an ice cream. Service was good. Pork chops was decent. But really nothing to write home about.

text.text:
The header, for this cafe, reads "Ai Cafe Singapore - Best Cafe Singapore" ....so much confidence! But, it is not although I would say that it can be one of the cafes which you may visit for a decent meal.
Located along Horne Road, the owner is friendly and accomodating.
The menu served mostly Western fare with a "out-of-the-blue" inclusion of Asian dish.
We had Mushroom soup which tasted as if they made it using mushrooms and not from powder nor cream.
The fried crab cakes and french fries were good although we all know they were frozen.
The chicken chop was sizeable and tasty.
The star, for this dinner, was the waffles which we topped with Belgian Dark Chocolate and Osmanthus ice-cream. The waffles was crispy, on the outside and soft inside, with a whiff of vanilla fragrance to  the batter.
Unfortunately, the lobster pow fun was a miss. We had a hard time getting the lobster flesh out of its shell. Also, the broth was not flavourful. Guess the broth was made when ordered and did not come from a labourous process of brewing the stock.
This cafe does not have the vibe of younger and newer ones in town. But if you are looking for a comfortable place, for gathering with old friends, where it's comfortable and can sit long, this is the place. Also good for family dinners as its menu can cater to many differing taste buds.
